<h2 id="pagetitle">Message from the President</h2>
<div class="page-body clearfix">
<table style="width: 550px;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left" valign="top"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-size: small;">Our name, INTEC, reflects the very essence of our company's goals and aspirations. We strive to be a highly sophisticated "Intellectual Echelon" (INT-EC) that utilizes Information Technology, International Tele-Communications, and Integrated Technology.</span></span>
<p>Our name also represents our guiding principle of the "Interlinking 7Cs," the first of which is "Interlink with Clients"― our fundamental commitment to always place clients' satisfaction first.</p>
<p>Since our establishment in 1964, INTEC has advanced the concept of " Computer Utility " ― the creation of an environment where anyone has access to computer technology anywhere and anytime, much as they would have access to electricity, gas, water, or any public utility.</p>
</td>
<td align="center" valign="top"><img src="../../cov/img/president.jpg" alt="President Koju Takizawa" border="0" height="182" width="120" /><br /> <span style="font-size: small;">President <br /> Koju Takizawa</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" align="left" valign="top">
<p>Now, with the imminent arrival of "Cloud Computing" thanks to the development of mobile technology and broadband communications, as well as the explosive rise of the Internet and the subsequent evolution of websites, INTEC has scaled up its concept of Computer Utility into the new vision: "IT in all, based on IT." We are endeavoring to further utilize IT in order to generate value-added services and bring benefits to society.</p>
<p>INTEC rises above its competitors by delivering comprehensive solutions that encompass outsourcing, network businesses, software development, and system integration, with a particular focus on the ultimate reliability of a 24 hours a day, 365 days a year nonstop operation.</p>
<p>With this competitive edge, we have developed and broadened our business, and have succeeded in earning the strong trust and confidence of many of the leading corporations in a wide spectrum of fields, including manufacturing, distribution, and finance, as well as local government.</p>
<p>In April 2008, INTEC Group became one of the top IT service conglomerates in Japan when we established IT Holdings through management integration with TIS. As corporations face increasingly diverse and complex needs, including information security, compliance, and risk management, INTEC intends to utilize our Group's integrated power.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
